<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Create a binary file from the given memory buffer.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The exact type of the binary file will be inferred automatically, and the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; appropriate implementation selected.  The context may be NULL except if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the resulting file is an LLVM IR file.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The memory buffer is not consumed by this function.  It is the responsibilty</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; of the caller to free it with \\c LLVMDisposeMemoryBuffer.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; If NULL is returned, the \\p ErrorMessage parameter is populated with the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; error&#39;s description.  It is then the caller&#39;s responsibility to free this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; message by calling \\c LLVMDisposeMessage.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="146"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; If there are no symbols, the result is NULL.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="147"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="148"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The returned iterator is merely a shallow copy. Nevertheless, it is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="149"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the responsibility of the caller to free it with</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="150"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; \\c LLVMDisposeSymbolIterator.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="151"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
